Key Investment Highlights

The NEXBA business has successfully restructured to Goodness Group Global Pty Ltd (GGG) and the opportunity to join this ambitious journey and invest is now open for the last time at the current valuation before the Group moves into a new phase of profitable expansion!

The Founders behind NEXBA, Troy Douglas & Drew Bilbe, have established the Group, consolidating their iconic Australian owned brand NEXBA under Goodness Group Global Pty Ltd, as they realise the shared vision in building a multi-market, multi-channel, multi-category portfolio of leading 'better-for-you' brands that is uniquely powered by the proprietary Goodsweet® sweetener, the Intel chip inside the NEXBA Brand.

The Goodness Group Global NEXBA BUSINESS PLAN is set to achieve a doubling of shareholder value based on industry standard EBITDA multiples over the next 3 to 5 years, with significant scope for further performance via expansion opportunities including M&A and other strategic partnerships.

If you are an existing investor, this is an exciting opportunity to increase your allocation with VentureCrowd as they expand from NEXBA to Goodness Group Global & progress on their profitable growth path.

Not a NEXBA investor yet? This is a unique opportunity to become a shareholder and join the ride!


  • Sugar-Free: Over 6 billion grams of sugar removed from global diets… and counting!
  • Gross Profit and EBITDA Growth: NEXBA business plan on track to double group gross profit % in FY23, with actions already taken in major EBITDA improvements for FY24.
  • Profitability Path: NEXBA Business Plan with a clear pathway to sustained profitability targeting Goodness Group Global Group Net Sales of $55M and EBITDA of $6.4M+ by FY27E, representing a CAGR of 20.5% from FY23F
  • Margin Structure Improvement: Operational shift to UK & European manufacturing, transforming EMEA Gross Margins vs previous importation from Australia.
  • ‘Beyond NEXBA’: In 2023 NEXBA Pty Ltd expanded to Goodness Group Global Pty Ltd with an ambitious strategy and a fast-to-market innovation model built on customer collaboration and new strategic partnerships, using their proprietary Goodsweet® sweetener to bring Naturally Sugar Free to more consumers and markets.
  • Multi-Market, Multi-Channel, Multi-Category: As they build their house of brands, including through new category M&A, they will exploit existing and emerging international partnerships to drive distribution, scale and profitable growth across their channels and markets. Focus on controlled costs with increased volume to support positive EBITDA & cash flow.
  • Goodsweet® sweetener: Branded Sugar Substitute ‘Intel Chip’ to play as a licensed ingredient in 3rd party brands, with most imminent example being The Cheesecake Shop Trial to launch in all 27 WA sites in June.

From the Founders: Cheers to you!

The world has evolved & as founders so have we.

13 years in and while NEXBA has not been immune to what many describe as an unprecedented & challenging environment (COVID & geo-political issues resulting in global supply chain constraints, rising inflation, and an instability in capital markets), it has cemented the growing market opportunity to deliver our vision. During the last 3 years we have maintained our strong domestic customer relationships and category presence, and built internationally, adding distribution in 9 new countries for NEXBA. We have the experience to deliver a multi-market, multi-channel, multi-category portfolio of leading 'better-for-you' brands.

As Founders we are proud of our team and our shareholders. We thank them & you for being a part of our NEXBA story. The NEXBA brand has set the foundations for our expansion to GOODNESS GROUP GLOBAL.

This next phase has already seen a step–change in executional excellence as we seek to capitalise on our strong customer partnerships, proprietary Goodsweet® sweetener & growing consumer demand for 'better-for-you' brands.

While sustainable growth will always be an important metric - accelerating profitability & scaling up impact is our commitment to maximising value for shareholders long-term.

Cheers to you!

Use of Funds and Exit Strategy

This ‘Series B’ capital raise extension offers the business the opportunity to execute a bolder business plan, to focus on delivering profitability in each division and ultimately create a stronger Goodness Group Global platform that will unlock greater value and liquidity options for all shareholders over time.

The Founders are seeking investors who share their vision to create positive change with brands that Taste Good & Do Good.

The Founders ambition is to continue the business beyond the next phase, further delivering internal governance and management expertise to enhance accountability and performance in mitigating risks and unlocking expansion opportunities.

Goodness Group Global is pursuing a final short term capital raise from existing shareholders and select aligned new investors who would represent a minority investment in the Group.

The Group aims to return to the capital markets at a superior valuation once they deliver on the business plan and expansion opportunities outlined. The Founders anticipate this to be a 3-5 year horizon and it is at this point they expect the opportunity for a significant liquidity event for all shareholders.

The promise of guilt free enjoyment connects with a consumer mindset that is universal across demographics, life-stage groups, beverage needs, and occasions.

Why NEXBA Expansion to Goodness Group Global

In 2023 the founders & shareholders of Nexba formed Goodness Group Global. Goodness Group Global’s purpose is ‘creating change for good, one sip and bite at a time!’

Goodness Group Global will be a Multi-Market, Multi-Category Brand Platform, proudly owned by passionate founders, underpinned by iconic Australian challenger brand NEXBA and powered by its proprietary and proven ‘Goodsweet®’ sweetener.

The health and wellness megatrend: Health, wellness and sustainability have become global megatrends, with foodtech and bevtech fast becoming two of the most important emerging investment sectors.

Consumers and the planet deserve better: However, the food and beverage industry is dominated by multinationals who have failed to put the health and wellness of consumers first. Goodness Group Global is committed to being founder driven with brands that, at their core, taste good and do good.

Put frankly, Goodness Group Global wants multinational food & beverage corporations to take notice and rethink sugar, artificial ingredient use & what is ‘good for the planet’.

Under Goodness Group Global, NEXBA will continue to champion the movement to remove sugar and artificials from consumption and the Goodsweet® sweetener will unlock incremental opportunities. Together, Goodness Group Global will transform health and wellness as the total brand portfolio will reduce sugar and artificial ingredient consumption in key food and beverage categories.

More accessible 'better-for-you' brands means more growth: Founded with purpose-led Australian brand, NEXBA, Goodness Group Global can create a step-jump in the value of the business as they activate synergies to make 'better-for-you' and the planet products more accessible and available to consumers.

Understanding The Goodsweet Difference

Their unique and universally applicable proprietary ‘Goodsweet®’ sweetener blend, developed over 6 years, allows NEXBA to emulate the taste profile of sugar in an unprecedented and all natural way. The Goodness Group Global will deliver further innovation with NEXBA brand & future owned brands & license Goodsweet® as an ingredient.

GOODSWEET® is differentiated by adding secret natural ingredients to its natural sweetener blend that makes the taste profile unparalleled to the competition.

Stevia/Erythritol based blends are not new to the market, however they do not emulate the taste profile of sugar.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue

‘Goodsweet®’is differentiated by adding secret natural ingredients to its sweetener blend that make the taste profile unparalleled to competition. After intensive sweetness is removed, only the natural, plant based building blocks of ‘Goodsweet®' remain.

Goodsweet® Sweetener is the ‘intel chip’ to ensure ‘no added sugar’ or ‘artificials’ exist within Goodness Group Global. Brands & Products can contain naturally occurring sugars that are good for you.

The Group's Proprietary Sweetener Blend is fully transferable to other Food & Beverage products with the same outcomes around sweetness, mouthfeel and aftertaste.

Goodsweet® Sweetener is already patented in Australia and patent pending in future key growth markets.

The Group continues to invest in and lead the development of the next generation of ‘Goodsweet®’ & an ongoing strategic patenting process.

Problem and Market

Consumers are gradually shifting towards sugar-free, all natural alternatives and healthier functional drinks. Traditional soft drinks companies focus on cost minimization vs delivering better-for-you for consumers. With sugar avoidance hitting the mainstream, younger generations are becoming increasingly sceptical about how sugar-free taste is achieved, driving a shift towards natural and more progressive products that better reflect their needs.

NEXBA not only disrupts the massive Soft Drinks category by removing billions of grams of sugar whilst maintaining a great and authentic taste, but also can take the lead in fast moving better-for-you emerging categories.

NEXBA’s core category, Kombucha, has already developed sales of $270M1 AUD in home market Australia growing 20%2 with growth of over 40%2 projected in other key markets for NEXBA including the UK.

Fees

Investors invest through a VentureCrowd Trust, which VentureCrowd manages as a single asset. We charge an annual management fee to investors, payable on exit and we only charge a performance fee where an exit delivers profit, thereby aligning ourselves with investor outcomes.

  • Contribution Fee: 1.1% This is the fee charged by the Trustee for the establishment of the Trust and the purchasing entity, structuring the overall investment and raising capital by way of issue of Units. Payable upon acceptance of your investment by the Trustee.
  • Management Fee: 1.65% per annum (charged on conversion or exit).
  • Performance Fee: 20% of the profit. We only charge a performance fee on conversion or exit.
